 navin agarwal chairman tom albanese chief executive officer dd jalan cfo products zinc lead oil and gas iron ore aluminium copper gold and silver revenue ₹ billion us billion  net income ₹ billion us billion  number of employees approx   website wwwvedantalimitedcom vedanta limited formerly known as sesa sterlitesesa goa limited a vedanta group company is one of the worlds largest global diversified natural resource majors with operations across zincleadsilver oil  gas iron ore copper aluminium and commercial power for more than five decades it has been engaged in exploration mining and processing of iron ore the company was founded in  as scambi economici sa goa since then it has grown to be one among the top lowcost producers of iron ore in the world during – it diversified into the manufacture of pig iron and metallurgical coke it has also developed indigenous and environmentfriendly technology for producing high quality metallurgical coke in  it became a majorityowned subsidiary of vedanta resources plc listed on the london stock exchange when vedanta acquired  controlling stake from mitsui  co ltd in june  sesa goa limited acquired vs dempo  co private limited now sesa resources limited along with its fully owned subsidiary dempo mining corporation now vedanta limited and  equity in goa maritime private limited in  vedanta acquired the zinc assets of british miner anglo american plc in  vedanta resources bought  controlling stake in cairn india indias largest private sector oil  gas company in  sterlite industries and sesa goa announced their merger and finally merged into a single entity in august  in  sesa sterlite changed its name to vedanta limited on april   cairn india merged with vedanta limited to consolidate its position as one of the largest diversified natural resources companies in the world vedanta limited’s operations are based predominantly in goa odisha rajasthan chhattisgarh tamil nadu karnataka punjab gujarat and andhra pradesh while offices are based across various locations in india contents  history  milestones  brief outline  milestones  products and operations  csr  sustainability  offices  see also  notes  external links and references history  milestonesedit brief outlineedit scambi economici societa anonyma sesa owned by baron ludovic toeplitz with the financial backing of alessandro vassalo obtained the orasso dongor mining lease in sirsaim goa in  and sesa goa limitada was formed it was bought over in  with equal shareholding by gewerkeshaft exploration e bergbau and ferromin spa a subsidiary of finsider spa of iri group which eventually acquired the other half stake in  sesa goa limitada was incorporated as a private limited company in  under the companies act  in  sesa goa private limited was formed with the merger of sesa goa limitada with another mining company in goa mingoa sociedade miniera goesa sarl in  sesa goa limited became a public limited company with  equity with indian shareholders in  mitsui  co ltd of japan acquired finsider international along with its  stake in sesa goa limited  in  vedanta resources plc acquired the controlling stake in sesa goa limited from mitsui  co ltd milestonesedit by  sesa goa and mingoa were incorporated as a private limited company under the companies act  the merger happened in  and the new unified company was called ‘sesa goa pvt ltd’ the company went public in  with  indian shareholders holding  of its shares and the remaining  held by finsider international which later became ilva international sesa goa had started with iron mining as its core business but slowly it ventured into barge construction in  at sirsaim located in the bardez taluka of north goa since then the barge construction unit has been developed into a shipbuilding division growth in the s in  the first phase of a  ton pig iron plant was commissioned in the same year sesa introduced india’s first lowphosphorus foundry grade pig iron in india and subsequently formalised the business under pig iron division the pig iron plant is located at amona goa this plant has an annual production capacity of  tonnes per annum other alliances were formed in the nineties—in january  sesa shipping was launched by acquiring transhipper mv orissa the year also saw the inclusion of  new coke ovens when mitsui  co of japan bought finsider international in  it gained  stake in sesa go by  sesa kembla became a  subsidiary of sesa goa in  a narrain mines located in chitradurga karnataka were purchased a supreme court directive in august  led to suspension of mining activities in the region in  sesa goa started mining operations in barbil which has the fifth largest deposit of iron ore and manganese in the world they started producing high grade iron ore which was exported from the port towns of haldia and paradip along with these business ventures in  the company started the sesa community development foundation that supported the ncm sesa technical school and a new sesa football academy the company promoted sesa fa mergers and acquisitions   onwards sesa kembla completed the creation of an indigenous and environmentfriendly technology that produced highquality metallurgical coke this technology generated power as a byproduct in  sesa group becomes the first business of its kind to be certified with ohsas  in  the sesa goa equity in sesa industries was raised to  impacting the shareholding pattern in  vedanta resources plc a diversified metals and mining group founded by anil agarwal acquired  controlling stake in sesa goa ltd from mitsui  co ltd vedanta resources is listed on the london stock exchange and a constituent of ftse  index the deal was worth ₹ billion us million making it the largest ma deal in the industry so far in  sesa goa acquired goabased dempo group’s mining and maritime businesses for ₹ billion us million in an allcash deal this was the second largest acquisition in india’s ironore industry and it gave sesa goa access to dempo’s  million tons of ironore mineable resources in goa in  sesa goa purchased  stake in western cluster liberia for  million the liberia gola forest community people who also suffered from the civil war believe that the coming of western cluster will help to alleviate their suffering and provide employment products and operationsedit zincleadsilver zinc india business is owned and operated by hindustan zinc limited hzl hzl owns and operates a fully integrated zinclead business hzl is one of the worlds largest integrated zinclead producers by volume sesa sterlite owns  of the share capital of hzl while the government of india remains an equity partner and holds a  stake hzl is listed on indian stock exchanges nse and bsehzls fully integrated zinc operations include five leadzinc mines one rock phosphate mine four hydrometallurgical zinc smelters two lead smelters one leadzinc smelter four sulphuric acid plants one silver refinery and six captive power plants at our chanderiya dariba and zawar facilities in the state of rajasthan processing and refining facilities for zinc at haridwar and for zinc lead and silver at pantnagar both in the state of uttarakhand and in northern india in fy  these operations delivered  tonnes of mined zinclead metalinconcentrate and  tonnes of refined zinc and lead oil  gas sesa sterlites oil  gas operations comprise the assets of cairn india in india sri lanka and south africa cairn india is indias largest privatesector crude oil producer contributing to over  of indias crude oil production sesa sterlite owns  of cairn india which is also the fastestgrowing asian ep company platts  and one of the top  independent ep companies worldwide cairn india has a worldclass resource base with interest in eight blocks in india one in sri lanka and one in south africa cairn indias resource base is located in four strategically focused areas  the onshore rjon rajasthan block two blocks on the west coast of india four blocks on the east coast of india including one in sri lanka and one block in south africa cairn indias rajasthan block is the largest onshore discovery in india in the last  years and has an estimated  billion barrels of oil equivalent in place with a basin potential to support a production rate of  barrels of oil per day cairn india has a strong track record of exploration with nearly  exploration success ratio it has initiated an exploration and appraisal programme to unlock further potential in the proven rajasthan block cairn india has a planned net capital investment of us billion through fy with around  of this investment allocated for the rajasthan block cairn india has a current operating capacity of  boepd at rajasthan and remains on track to deliver a fy exit production target of over  boepd the company has recently commenced gas sales from the rajasthan block sesa sterlites oil  gas operations comprise the assets of cairn india in india sri lanka and south africa cairn india is indias largest private sector crude oil producer contributing to over  of indias crude oil production iron oresesa sterlite is largest private sector exporter of iron ore in india and is developing large iron ore deposits in liberia iron ore mining operations are carried out in the indian states of goa and karnataka we also manufacture pig iron and metallurgical coke during fy  our indian iron ore operations were affected by a suspension of iron ore mining activities across the states of goa and karnataka the honourable supreme court allowed resumption of karnataka mine in april  subject to statutory clearances subsequent to receiving all the approvals they have started mining in karnataka from  december  in  sesa goa limited had acquired iron ore assets in liberia with around  billion in reserves and resources across three deposits  bomi hills bea mountain and mano river located at a distance of  kilometers from the port at monrovia extensive drilling at our liberia assets has confirmed a billion tonne of iron ore deposit last year with further multifold upside currently they are reviewing the different phased options including the first phase of  million tons sesa sterlite is largest private sector exporter of iron ore in india its subsidiary western cluster ltd is developing large iron ore deposits in liberia copper they says we aim to provide highquality refined copper by improving our operational efficiency and reducing our unit costs their copper business is principally a custom smelting operation located in india and australia our indian operations include a smelter refinery phosphoric acid plant sulphuric acid plant and copper rod plant at thoothukudi in southern india sesa sterlite owns  of the mt lyell copper mine in tasmania australia which produces a portion of the total requirement of copper concentrate at our indian operations production of cathodes at our copper india business was kt in fy  our australian operations produced kt of mined metal in fy sesa sterlite copper business is located in india it also owns  stake in copper mines of tasmania pty ltd australia aluminium balco has a smelter capacity of  ktpa with capabilities to produce ingots wirerods billets busbars and rolled products balcos operations include mines refineries smelters and captive power plants in the state of chhattisgarh in india sesa sterlite holds a controlling  stake in balco while the government of india remains an equity partner and holds the remaining  stake the korbaii balco smelter produces  ktpa of aluminium and they are expanding production capacity to  ktpa with the commencement of the new korbaiii  ktpa smelter in fy balcos current operations have access to captive power from  mw thermal power plant a new  mw power plant is expected to commence production soon power sesa sterlite is one of indias leading power producers with a capacity of  mw in commercial power they have commercial power generation business which currently operates  mw jharsuguda power plant in odisha  mw balco power plant in chhattisgarh  mw malco power plant in tamil nadu and  mw hzl wind power plants at various locations in india they are also setting up a  mw talwandi sabo power plant in the state of punjab talwandi sabo power limited a  subsidiary of sesa sterlite is setting up a  mw thermal power project in punjab with the first unit starting operations by q fy hindustan zinc has  mw of wind power generational capacity making it one of the largest producers of wind power in india malco operates a  mw plant metallurgical coke approximately  of total production is consumed by sesa group for its pig iron production the remainder is sold to customers located in india sesa goa has patented a technology that provides high quality output and produces power it is a patented and follows a twoproduct process with metallurgical coke as the main product and the sensible heat of the exhaust flue gas as a coproduct this heat can be used for producing clean electricity the company uses nonpolluting nonrecovery australian technology at the plant in amona negative pressure in the ovens ensures no polluting leakages pig iron this business is skewed towards catering to the steel mills and foundries of the indian market in particular the western and southern india the division manufactures basic foundry and nodular grade pig iron and also sells slag the annual production capacity is  tons per annum csr  sustainabilityedit vedanta invested us  million towards community development in  benefitting over  million people globally the confederation of indian indusry cii ranked vedanta limited and its subsidiary hindustan zinc among the top ten sustainable firms in india in fy vedanta recycled  of the fly ash generated through operations as well as recycled  of the water utilized during its operations the company has entered into a first of its kind unique publicprivatepartnership ppp with the ministry of women and child development government of india to modernize and construct the anganwadi infrastructure in india with the aim to supplement inclusive economic growth in india vedanta focuses on women empowerment through its csr initiatives the companys csr initiatives  rural women through the creation of about  self help groups in the communities across the locations of its operations officesedit the registered office and corporate office of vedanta limited are based in mumbai the company has offices in new delhi ncr as well as across its operations in the country see alsoedit companies portal mining portal mining in india list of mines in india notesedit  a b consolidated results for the fourth quarter and full year ended  march  pdf retrieved  june    httpprofitndtvcomcorporatecompanyhistorysesagoaltdmicrosluglivebudget  our bureau  vedanta to merge sesa goa sterlite ind in allshare deal  business line thehindubusinesslinecom retrieved    a b sesa goa buys dempos mining biz  business standard news businessstandardcom retrieved    utpal bhaskar  vedanta’s cairn india stake buy completed livemint retrieved    sesa goa sterlite combine to reduce debt of parent vedanta archived from the original on  august  retrieved  june    sesa sterlite renamed as vedanta ltd the hindu  retrieved    et bureau april   cairn india merges with vedanta economictimesindiatimescom retrieved june     vedanta limited wwwvedantalimitedcom retrieved  june    sesa goa volume expansion to drive growth archived from the original on  september  retrieved  june    httpwwwedelweissinmarketinformationaspxcocodetbch  the hindu business line  ffe minerals ties up with sesa kembla for coke oven thehindubusinesslinein  retrieved    vedanta chairman speech  vedanta ltd chairman speech economictimesindiatimescom  retrieved    archive news the hindu retrieved    vedanta bags mitsui’s  in miner sesa goa indian express  retrieved    panaji dhns sesa goa buys dempo mining firm deccanheraldcom retrieved    sesa goa acquires dempo mining « weeksupdate weeksupdatecom  retrieved    pti  sesa goa to buy  stake in w