any see sesa fa vedanta limited type public limited traded as bse  nse sesagoa nyse sslt bse sensex constituent industry mining founded  headquarters new delhi  india key people anil agarwal chairman emeritus navin agarwal chairman tom albanese chief executive officer dd jalan cfo products zinc lead oil and gas iron ore aluminium copper gold and silver revenue ₹ billion us billion  net income ₹ billion us billion  number of employees approx   website wwwvedantalimitedcom vedanta limited formerly known as sesa sterlitesesa goa limited a vedanta group company is one of the worlds largest global diversified natural resource majors with operations across zincleadsilver oil  gas iron ore copper aluminium and commercial power for more than five decades it has been engaged in exploration mining and processing of iron ore the company was founded in  as scambi economici sa goa since then it has grown to be one among the top lowcost producers of iron ore in the world during – it diversified into the manufacture of pig iron and metallurgical coke it has also developed indigenous and environmentfriendly technology for producing high quality metallurgical coke in  it became a majorityowned subsidiary of vedanta resources plc listed on the london stock exchange when vedanta acquired  controlling stake from mitsui  co ltd in june  sesa goa limited acquired vs dempo  co private limited now sesa resources limited along with its fully owned subsidiary dempo mining corporation now vedanta limited and  equity in goa maritime private limited in  vedanta acquired the zinc assets of british miner anglo american plc in  vedanta resources bought  controlling stake in cairn india indias largest private sector oil  gas company in  sterlite industries and sesa goa announced their merger and finally merged into a single entity in august  in  sesa sterlite changed its name to vedanta limited on april   cairn india merged with vedanta limited to consolidate its position as one of the largest diversified natural resources companies in the world vedanta limited’s operations are based predominantly in goa odisha rajasthan chhattisgarh tamil nadu karnataka punjab gujarat and andhra pradesh while offices are based across various locations in india contents  history  milestones  brief outline  milestones  products and operations  csr  sustainability  offices  see also  notes  external links and references history  milestonesedit brief outlineedit scambi economici societa anonyma sesa owned by baron ludovic toeplitz with the financial backing of alessandro vassalo obtained the orasso dongor mining lease in sirsaim goa in  and sesa goa limitada was formed it was bought over in  with equal shareholding by gewerkeshaft exploration e bergbau and ferromin spa a subsidiary of finsider spa of iri group which eventually acquired the other half stake in  sesa goa limitada was incorporated as a private limited company in  under the companies act  in  sesa goa private limited was formed with the merger of sesa goa limitada with another mining company in goa mingoa sociedade miniera goesa sarl in  sesa goa limited became a public limited company with  equity with indian shareholders in  mitsui  co ltd of japan acquired finsider international along with its  stake in sesa goa limited  in  vedanta resources plc acquired the controlling stake in sesa goa limited from mitsui  co ltd milestonesedit by  sesa goa and mingoa were incorporated as a private limited company under the companies act  the merger happened in  and the new unified company was called ‘sesa goa pvt ltd’ the company went public in  with  indian shareholders holding  of its shares and the remaining  held by finsider international which later became ilva international sesa goa had started with iron mining as its core business but slowly it ventured into barge construction in  at sirsaim located in the bardez taluka of north goa since then the barge construction unit has been developed into a shipbuilding division growth in the s in  the first phase of a  ton pig iron plant was commissioned in the same year sesa introduced india’s first lowphosphorus foundry grade pig iron in india and subsequently formalised the business under pig iron division the pig iron plant is located at amona goa this plant has an annual production capacity of  tonnes per annum other alliances were formed in the nineties—in january  sesa shipping was launched by acquiring transhipper mv orissa the year also saw the inclusion of  new coke ovens when mitsui  co of japan bought finsider international in  it gained  stake in sesa go by  sesa kembla became a  subsidiary of sesa goa in  a narrain mines located in chitradurga karnataka were purchased a supreme court directive in august  led to suspension of mining activities in the region in  sesa goa started mining operations in barbil which has the fifth largest deposit of iron ore and manganese in the world they started producing high grade iron ore which was exported from the port towns of haldia and paradip along with these business ventures in  the company started the sesa community development foundation that supported the ncm sesa technical school and a new sesa football academy the company promoted sesa fa mergers and acquisitions   onwards sesa kembla completed the creation of an indigenous and environmentfriendly technology that produced highquality metallurgical coke this technology generated power as a byproduct in  sesa group becomes the first business of its kind to be certified with ohsas  in  the sesa goa equity in sesa industries was raised to  impacting the shareholding pattern in  vedanta resources plc a diversified metals and mining group founded by anil agarwal acquired  controlling stake in sesa goa ltd from mitsui  co ltd vedanta resources is listed on the london stock exchange and a constituent of ftse  index the deal was worth ₹ billion us million making it the largest ma deal in the industry so far in  sesa goa acquired goabased dempo group’s mining and maritime businesses for ₹ billion us million in an allcash deal this was the second largest acquisition in india’s ironore industry and it gave sesa goa access to dempo’s  million tons of ironore mineable resources in goa in  sesa goa purchased  stake in western cluster liberia for  million the liberia gola forest community people who also suffered from the civil war believe that the coming of western cluster will help to alleviate their suffering and provide employment products and operationsedit zincleadsilver zinc india business is owned and operated by hindustan zinc limited hzl hzl owns and operates a fully integrated zinclead business hzl is one of the worlds largest integrated zinclead producers by volume sesa sterlite owns  of the share capital of hzl while the government of india remains an equity partner and holds a  stake hzl is listed on indian stock exchanges nse and bsehzls fully integrated zinc operations include five leadzinc mines one rock phosphate mine four hydrometallurgical zinc smelters two lead smelters one leadzinc smelter four sulphuric acid plants one silver refinery and six captive power plants at our chanderiya dariba and zawar facilities in the state of rajasthan processing and refining facilities for zinc at haridwar and for zinc lead and silver at pantnagar both in the state of uttarakhand and in northern india in fy  these operations delivered  tonnes of mined zinclead metalinconcentrate and  tonnes of refined zinc and lead oil  gas sesa sterlites oil  gas operations comprise the assets of cairn india in india sri lanka and south africa cairn india is indias largest privatesector crude oil producer contributing to over  of indias crude oil production sesa sterlite owns  of cairn india which is also the fastestgrowing asian ep company platts  and one of the top  independent ep companies worldwide cairn india has a worldclass resource base with interest in eight blocks in india one in sri lanka and one in south af